TVC News journalist Babajide Akolade Otitoju, was full of praise for Manchester United forward, Cristiano Ronaldo. He expressed the joy to have watched the Portugal international play. He went on to say that he was proud to have named his son after him.
Recall that Cristiano Ronaldo was at his usual best on Saturday as he single handedly put Norwich to the sword. The striker managed to grab a hat trick, leading United to a 3-2 victory.
While reacting to Ronaldo’s performance, the award winning investigative journalist took to his facebook page to write a message that read thus;
“21 goals for the season, 15 goals in the toughest league in the world at 37 years of age. 60th career hat trick. There’ll never be another you, Ronaldo. I am not honored to watch the greatest scorer of all time play, I bless the day I named my second son after you, Cristiano Ronaldo.”



